                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="25"><font size="3">New Caledonia</font></td>
                      <td align="right"><font size="3"><img src="../../img/flags/flg_n-cal.gif" width="70" height="35"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" height="1">
                    <tr background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif" valign="top"> 
                      <td background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_space.gif" width="37" height="1"></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <p class="profile_intro">New Caledonia, the fourth largest producer 
                    of nickel in the world, has one of the highest average incomes 
                    per capita in the Pacific. Although still part of France, 
                    it is quickly gaining responsibility for most aspects of government 
                    under the status of 'shared sovereignty'. 
                  <p align="center"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_n-caledon.gif" width="386" height="188" alt="Map of New Caledonia"></p>
                  <br>
                  <h5><a name="facts"></a>Facts and Figures</h5>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="statbox" bgcolor="#99cc33">
